translation.p:
(L. 8.) Of (this), one hundred-and-sixtieth (vēli) and one three-hundred-and-twentieth;
1/320 of nine twentieths and three eightieths; and (1/320) of three quarters and three eightieths
(is) second-crop land.

(L. 5.) (He) cut off a finger of Vīra-Kēraḷa and saw (his) back (i.e). put him to flight);
(but), when (the latter) came and bowed (to him), (he) bestowed riches (on him) in public Literally, ‘so that the (whole) earth knew (it).’ and
gave (him) to eat from the (royal) plates.
